headline.main: WASHINGTON.; The Deficiency Bill--Mr. Webster--The Garay Grant--Fish.

docs.lead_paragraph: The internecine conflict is decided. The Senate have beat the House by 50,000 majority, and tomorrow the Deficiency bill will be a law. The Committees of Conference have come together, and, considering the weighty reason in favor of an agreement on that measure, not less in the aggregate than five and a half millions, have come to an understanding. headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY; HEALTH OF THE CITY HEALTH COMMISSIONER. FIRE THE NINETEENTH WARD ELECTION CASE. LOOK OUT FOR THE IMPOSTERS. THE LUNDAY'S LANE CELEBRATION. THE FIRE DEPARTMENT INSPECTOR OF ELECTIONS. STOLEN PROPERTY. POST-OFFICE NOTICE. ACCIDENT BY FALLING.

docs.lead_paragraph: HEALTH OF THE CITY.-There is a frightful increase in the number of deaths that have occurred during the past week, as compared with the deaths of the 'week ending July 10. Then there were but 332 deathsthis week the number reaches 466, an increase of 134. Of those who died, 64 were men, 52 women, 206 boys, and 144 girls :-13 died by apoplexy.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamer Philadelphia, McGOWAN, sails today, for your city. The passengers are generally healthy and in good spirits. Through the salubrious atmosphere of Sand Key and the attention of our port physician, the cholera has entirely disappeared, and health and cleanliness is once more restored.

byline.original: Correspondece of the New-York Daily Times

docs.lead_paragraph: It is stated that the endowment of the Professorship of Moral Philosophy In Hamilton College, is succeeding well. Rev. Dr. Lathrop has recently announced that at least two-thirds of the required fifteen thousand dollars would be securely by the time the Commencement occurs. The Auburn Christian Advocate learns that the amount already subscribed exceeds that estimate. The remainder will not be long delayed.
